        "created_at": "2025-05-18T20:07:26.550Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I would like to propoosit that the website updates the linux signal desktop installation instructions to make use of <a href=\"https://manpages.debian.org/bookworm/extrepo/extrepo.1p.en.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">extrepo</a>,   it would reduce the steps and improve readabiltiy</p>\n<p><strong>Old method</strong></p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">wget -O- https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt/keys.asc | gpg --dearmor &gt; signal-desktop-keyring.gpg;\n\ncat signal-desktop-keyring.gpg | sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/signal-desktop-keyring.gpg &gt; /dev/null\n\necho 'deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/signal-desktop-keyring.gpg] https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt xenial main' |  sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/signal-xenial.list\n\nsudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install signal-desktop\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong><code>extrepo</code> method</strong></p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">sudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install extrepo -y   # only needed if exrepo not present\n\nsudo extrepo enable signal   # sets up the offical signal repo and keys\n\nsudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt -y install signal-desktop  # update and install desktop\n\n</code></pre>",
