        "cooked": "<p>Does Signal maintain their own packages for Linux distribution?</p>\n<p>Also, I donâ€™t believe that Signal officially supports (or supports at all) a package distribution for Fedora Linux (workstation or server).  If they do, I canâ€™t find it after a lot of looking around.</p>\n<p>Signal should support Fedora without requiring the use of package managers other than dnf.  And it not require the installation of a bunch of other libraries.</p>\n<p>I just upgraded from Fedora 41 to Fedora 42.  Iâ€™m not going to install Signal as I get warnings of library conflicts when checking the installation of the necessary libraries.</p>",
